[6] Taiwan
Date: Sat 07 Jul 2007
Source: Radio Taiwan International [edited]
<http://english.rti.org.tw/Content/GetSingleNews.aspx?ContentID=39878>

The Ministry of Heath confirmed on Friday [6 Jul
2007] the 1st indigenous case of dengue
hemorrhagic fever in Taiwan this year. A
68-year-old woman from Tainan in southern Taiwan
is now in a stable condition after treatment.
Numerous cases of dengue fever, which is
transmitted by mosquitoes, are reported in Taiwan
each year. The hemorrhagic variation of the
disease can be particularly life threatening if
patients do not receive quick treatment.
The Department of Health also said that a further
14 cases of indigenous dengue fever have been
reported in the same district in Tainan.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett
