[7] India (Borivili)
Date: 07 Jul 2007
Source: Daily News and Analysis [edited]
<http://www.dnaindia.com/report.asp?NewsID=1108653>

Unconfirmed reports say [a man], [age] 22, a
Borivli resident, died of dengue on Thursday [5
Jul 2007]. He was admitted to the Karuna Hospital
in Borivli. He also suffered from brain
haemorrhage. However, he remained non-comittal.
He said the hospital would seek a 2nd opinion on
whether the death was because of dengue.
Meanwhile, at least 254 new cases with
monsoon-related diseases were admitted to
municipal hospitals in the last 24 hours. In the
last 5 days [2-6 Jul 2007], the civic hospitals
reported 815 cases of monsoon-related diseases.
Officials from the health department said 205 of
these were discharged after treatment. [The
number of dengue infections among these cases is not specified. - Mod.TY]
Medical practitioners projected a further rise in
such cases after 9 Jul [2007]. According to Dr.
SN Acharya, the incubation period for the virus
is usually 7 - 10 days after the 1st spell of rains.
[Byline: Sandeep Ashar]
--
