[8] Palau
Date: Tue 03 Jul 2007
Source: Radio New Zealand [edited]
<http://www.rnzi.com/pages/news.php?op=read&id=33387>

Palau's Ministry of Health reports there are now
14 confirmed cases of dengue fever. The Bureau of
Public Health Director, Stevenson Kuartei, says
there are 36 suspected cases of dengue, bringing the total figure to 50.
Mr. Kuartei says the Avian Flu Task Force, which
has been earlier asked by President Tommy
Remengesau to address the dengue outbreak, has
met to discuss the problem. The Task Force is
mobilising the community to conduct an
island-wide cleanup that will focus on getting rid of mosquito breeding sites.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Brent Barrett
[Palau is a member island of the Federated States
of Micronesia, and is located in the far western
region of the Caroline Islands. It has an area of
508 sq km (196 sq miles) and a population of 20 400 inhabitants.
A map of Palau showing its location within
Oceania, with additional information about the
island, can be accessed at:
<http://worldatlas.com/webimage/countrys/oceania/pw.htm> - Mod.TY.]
