[10] Honduras
Date: 7 Jul 2007
Source: Prensa Latina [accessable by subscription only, edited]
<http://www.plenglish.com/article.asp?ID=%7B9E6C3DCC-5DDC-4335-A9B0-6353A7217426%7D)&language=EN>

Reports of dengue cases in Honduras has markedly
increased over the weekend [30 Jun - 1 Jul 2007],
with about 5000 people infected from the classic
strain, and over 200 by dengue hemorrhagic fever,
health authorities revealed Saturday [7 Jul
2007]. The disease keeps spreading alarmingly,
and in the last 7 days, hemorrhagic cases
amounted to 221, and classic ones to 4737, Health
Minister Jenny Meza disclosed.
The number of people infected with the 2 types of
the virus so far this year [2007] almost doubled
that of the same period last year, according to Meza.
Meanwhile, it was revealed this morning that new
health facilities will be fitted out in the
capital to cope with the huge number of patients.
The Honduran health ministry reported 2 people
have died of the dengue hemorrhagic fever so far.
--
Communicated by:
ProMED Rapporteur Brent Barrett
[This article mentions the 2 dengue virus types.
There are, in fact, 4 dengue viruses. Perhaps
this article implies that 2 virus types are
co-circulating in Honduras. ProMED requests clarification.
A map of Honduras can be accessed at:
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/honduras.jpg>. - Mod.TY.]
